Differentiate between array_shift() and array_unshift() in PHP.

Function	          Description	                                                    Example
array_shift()	      Removes the first element from an array and returns it.         Reindexes array	$removed = array_shift($arr);
array_unshift()	    Adds one or more elements to the beginning of an array	        array_unshift($arr, "new");
  
CODE:
<?php
$colors = array("red", "green", "blue");

// Remove first element
$removed = array_shift($colors);
echo "Removed: $removed <br>";
print_r($colors);

// Add elements at the beginning
array_unshift($colors, "yellow", "purple");
echo "<br>After adding: ";
print_r($colors);
?>

OUTPUT:
Removed: red 
Array ([0] => green [1] => blue)
After adding: 
Array([0] => yellow [1] => purple [2] => green [3] => blue)
